skeletal remains: Most of the skull and a portion of the skeleton was recovered. The skull consists of: both maxillas, right premaxilla, nasals, both lacrimals, left postorbital, both quadrates, both jugals, left squamosal, both quadratojugals, left pterygoid, both palatines, left ectopterygoid, right epipterygoid, both dentaries, right surangular, right prearticular, the right splenial, right coronoid, a partial braincase, and 49 loose, rooted teeth. The skeleton has both scapulae and coracoids, 1 astragalus; the right ischium; 8 caudals; 
