skeletal remains: The skull is very incomplete, consisting of a right postorbital and squamosal. The skeleton consists of 2 cervical 3 sacral and a series of 6 midcaudal vertebrae, along with 6 chevrons and a rib. Pelvic girdle elements include: the left pubis and ischium and the distal blade of the right ilium. There is a partial leg consisting of the left tibia, fibula, and the astragalus (
Sampson and Loewen 2005
).

